OTHER_NOTES: I picked up 3 dogs in 2018, placed them on my truck and transported them home.

4 dogs were picked up by animal control and transported to animal hospitals for owners who were elderly or disabled and unable to transport the dogs themselves.

MISC_NOTES: Dog named "Java" reported stolen after dispute over adoption contract, which was never signed. First point of contact: Giles County Sheriff's Office and Giles County CWA, since this was adopter's county of residence, who had Java in temporary foster custody after Pocahontas Dog Training program. Dog subsequently disappeared, presumably concealed at PSCC with the full consent of Warden Stan Young. I contacted Tazewell County Sheriff's Office who maintained it was a civil matter and declined to investigate. Then contacted Michelle Welch with the SAG's office as well as Harold Clarke with VDOC. Learned from a former corrections officer named Danny Link that Warden Young contacted a rescue he is affiliated with (Augusta Dog Adoptions) acting as if the PSCC dog program was a releasing agency and stating they needed to place some dogs. I then contacted a representative from Augusta Dog Adoptions but she said they had not received Java.
